docs.text: if there's one thing i just can't stand , it's a film that oozes with sentimentality .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: here's a note to all film makers : films are more effective when the emotions of the characters speak for themselves .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: swelling , saddening music is not a good way to tell us that the people in the film are unhappy , and that the situation is hopeless .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: alas , my giant is a film that uses manipulative sentimentality so frequently and with such high intensity that i forgot as i watched it that there are other ways of getting audience members choked up .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: what reminded me was that i wasn't choked up , or even the slightest bit moved , for that matter .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: my giant is a forced , contrived , and conspicuously un-cute ( i detest the word " cute " but i've chosen to use it because the makers clearly wanted to create a " cute " film here ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it takes a premise that might have been interesting ( i liked the preview ) , and bogs it down with endless plot turns and cliches , all of which are intended to get some kind of easy emotional rise from the audience .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: maybe it will work for some people .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it didn't work for me .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: billy crystal plays sam cayman , an agent who , at the beginning of the film , is in romania .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: he's in romania because the kid actor he made famous is doing a film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: the screenplay has him in romania so he can get fired , get in a car accident , and get saved by an enormous individual who stands almost eight feet tall .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: his name is max ( gheorghe muresan ) , and sam thinks he'd be a great movie star because of his size .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: subplots are as follows : sam has a son and a wife ( kathleen quinlan ) , and he's never around for them , so they move to chicago .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: max is in love with a woman named lilianna who moved away from romania twenty years before the film begins .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: sam convinces max to go back to america with him so they can make lots of money , and so their various subplots can all be resolved .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: my giant , as a comedy , is only moderately funny .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: it has its moments , the best of which features steven seagal making fun of himself .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: in one great scene , sam gets his son on the phone to talk to seagal ; of course , his son doesn't believe that he's actually speaking to seagal , and he goes off about how bad of an actor he is ( i would quote the line i like but it would probably lose its effect ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: crystal is always entertaining , and he has a few good lines here ( some of which are subtle throwaways that many will miss entirely ) ; often , however , he's countered by a slew of jokes that aren't funny , and cause an involuntary rolling of the eyes .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: muresan is kind of fun to watch , but he just can't act very well .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: quinlan , on the other hand , is a great actress who needs to get a role that shows off her talents .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: she was underused last year in both event horizon and breakdown , but at least in those films she had moments in which she could show us her stuff .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: here , the best thing she gets to do is fake a romanian accent .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: all of these disappointing ingredients create a film that , for much of its running time , is simply mediocre .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: as my giant lumbers to its inevitable conclusion , however , director michael lehmann ( who did a great job directing the underrated hudson hawk ) and scriptwriter david seltzer pile on every cliche imaginable , each one intended specifically to pull at our heartstrings .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: sam's multiple engagements with his family are all completely hackneyed ( how about a main character who has a healthy relationship with his family ? ) .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: later , it turns out the entire story is supposed to be a great big metaphor signifying sam's reunion with his family .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and some people might think that what sam does for max towards the end is a valiant thing , but i had a few morality problems with it ( and i apologize for being vague ) .

docs.text: my giant could have been a straightforward and funny family film .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: more importantly , it could have been moving on a level far deeper than it is .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: instead , it's a complicated , overlong , and under-engaging film that elicits too few laughs and strives for superficial tears .
docs.label: negative

docs.text: and since it left me feeling completely unmoved , i stand by my position that sentimentality is evil and will ultimately destroy the world .
